ShopMee E-Commerce Platform - Bug Reports Log

This document tracks the defects identified during the testing phase of the ShopMee E-Commerce Platform. It serves as a transparent portfolio artifact demonstrating defect analysis, lifecycle tracking, and documentation structure.

Detailed Defect Log

| Bug ID | Bug Title | Module | Environment | Preconditions | Steps to Reproduce | Actual Result | Expected Result | Severity | Priority | Status |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :---: | :---: | :---: |
| **BUG-001** | SQL Injection vulnerability in the Email field on the Registration form. | User Registration | Staging-v1.4 | Registration page is displayed. | Input a malicious SQL payload into the Email field and click Register. | System crashes and displays the full database log trace on the UI. | The system must sanitize inputs and display a standard, secure generic error message. | `Critical` | **High** | `Open` |
| **BUG-002** | Session cookie missing mandatory HttpOnly and Secure flags. | Login | Staging-v1.4 | User is logged in successfully. | Inspect the JWT token cookie attributes in the Application tab of Developer Tools. | The session cookie can be accessed and read directly via client-side script (XSS vulnerability). | Cookies storing session data must have HttpOnly and Secure flags enabled to prevent data theft. | `High` | **High** | `Open` |
| **BUG-003** | No rate-limiting implemented on the Forgot Password form. | Forgot Password | Staging-v1.4 | Forgot Password page is displayed. | Use Postman Runner to send 100 consecutive password reset requests within 10 seconds. | All 100 requests are processed successfully, spamming the mail server with duplicate links. | System should limit requests to 1 per minute and return an HTTP 429 Too Many Requests status code. | `Medium` | *Low* | `Open` |
| **BUG-004** | Product variant price does not update correctly on the Product Detail page. | Product Detail | Staging-v1.4 | Viewing 'iPhone 14 Pro' product page. | Change storage variant from base 128GB to premium 512GB. | Displayed price remains at the base price of $999 despite different configuration in the DB. | The UI display price must dynamically update to $1299 corresponding to the selected variant. | `High` | **High** | `Open` |
| **BUG-005** | Modifying product quantity in the shopping cart does not recalculate the total price. | Shopping Cart | Staging-v1.4 | Items are added to the shopping cart. | Click the '+' button to increase the quantity of an item from 1 to 3. | Quantity text updates to 3 but the subtotal and taxes remain at the 1-item price level. | The system must automatically and instantly recalculate the total cart invoice when quantities change. | `High` | **Medium** | `Open` |
| **BUG-006** | Shopping cart page crashes (White Screen) when a product's stock drops to 0. | Shopping Cart | Staging-v1.4 | Product is already added to the cart. | Simulate a DB update reducing the product stock to 0 while user has the cart open. | Refreshing the '/cart' page results in an HTTP 500 Null Pointer Exception screen. | The cart should load normally with a warning: 'Product out of stock, please remove to proceed'. | `High` | **High** | `Open` |
| **BUG-007** | Place Order button allows multiple consecutive clicks, causing duplicate orders. | Checkout | Staging-v1.4 | At the final step of the checkout process. | Click the 'Place Order' button rapidly 3 times in a row. | System creates 3 identical orders in the database and charges the user account 3 times. | The Place Order button must be disabled immediately after the first click to prevent duplicates. | `High` | **High** | `Open` |

